The red and blue lights flashed in the night sky. The cop car pulled up next to the car. The officer got out of his car and walked up to the driver’s side of the car.

“License and registration,” the officer said.

The driver handed the officer his license and registration. The officer looked at the driver’s license and then looked at the car.

“Do you know why I pulled you over?” the officer asked.

The driver shook his head.

“You were going 100 miles per hour in a 55 mile per hour zone,” the officer said.

The driver looked at the officer in surprise. “I didn’t know I was going that fast,” he said.

The officer looked at the driver for a moment and then handed him his license and registration.

“I’m going to give you a warning this time,” the officer said. “But if I catch you going that fast again, you’ll get a ticket.”

The driver thanked the officer and drove away.

The driver looks at the officer in surprise, and the officer says, "I'm going to give you a warning this time, but if I catch you going that fast again, you'll get a ticket." The driver thanks the officer and drives away. The officer turns to his partner and says, "I'm not sure about that driver. He seems a bit too calm for someone who was just caught speeding." His partner shrugs and says, "Maybe he's just in shock. I've seen people react differently to getting pulled over." The officer nods and says, "Let's follow him and make sure he doesn't do anything else suspicious." They follow the car for a few miles and watch as the driver pulls into a gas station. The officer and his partner get out of their car and walk up to the driver's side of the car. The officer says, "License and registration," and the driver hands them over. The officer looks at the driver's license and then looks at the car. He says, "Do you know why I pulled you over?" The driver shakes his head, and the officer says, "You were speeding."
